      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the breakdown. so if the load increases at the very tip of the balcony, the torque increases significantly because of that length multiplier, right? i'm worried about what happens to the internal stress if the load isn't perfectly distributed. does the structural integrity depend more on the material strength or just the anchor point's ability to hold that moment?",
